And which part of leave do you want? Leave said we'd be able to have free trade with Europe AND be able to control freedom of movement. Remain said there was no way that that could happen! The electorate decided to believe REMAIN. If the government can get a deal that gives both free trade AND complete control of who works here then that would be all well and good, and we could go ahead and """"Leave"""". BUT the reality is most likely to be that REMAIN were right and we can have one or the other but not both. THAT is the reason we need parliament to have a say, so that we get what we think best matches what the people want. But you know what... I have NO IDEA what the people would want if they could only get one of those things!It IS NOT about trying to derail Brexit at all, it is simply just about ensuring that when it happens, it is in line with a majority vote in parliament (who will act in the best interests of the country one would hope) and not just the version of Brexit that Theresa May thinks is best.
